## Overview
Simple SQL database to track customers, egg sales, and expenses for a poultry farm. Provides monthly profit reports, customer rankings, and cost-per-sale analysis.

## Schema
- *customers*: Stores buyer information.
- *egg_sales*: Tracks each sale with quantity, unit price, and auto-calculated total.
- *expenses*: Records farm expenditures. Includes an optional \sale_id\ to link direct costs (like transport) to specific sales.

## Key Queries & Features
| Feature | Implementation |
| :--- | :--- |
| Total sales per customer | Simple CTE with \JOIN\ and \GROUP BY\ |
| Monthly Revenue/Expenses/Profit | Multi-CTE with \UNION\ (MySQL-compatible full outer join) |
| Customer Ranking | \RANK\, \DENSE_RANK\, \ROW_NUMBER\ window functions |
| Running Sales Total | Window function with \PARTITION BY customer\ |
| Cost-per-Sale Margin | Left join expenses on \sale_id\ |

## Sample Data
Includes 3 customers and 9 sales across Jan–Mar 2026. Expenses are split between *overhead* (Feed, Labor, Utilities) and *direct costs* (Transport linked to specific sales). The data shows a loss in January and profits in February/March to demonstrate realistic variance.

## Constraints & Integrity
- \CHECK\ constraints ensure positive quantities, prices, and amounts.
- Foreign keys use \ON DELETE CASCADE\ (customers) and \ON DELETE SET NULL\ (expenses) to maintain referential integrity.

## Quick Reference
- *Database*: MySQL (compatible with PostgreSQL with minor date-function changes).
- *Total Tables*: 3.
- *Window Functions Used*: 4 types.
- *Total Size*: < 50 KB (unzipped).`;

